subject: p19623993
History: Nasogastric tube manipulation. Evaluation for location.
Findings: The nasogastric tube is at the level of the pylorus. Nasoenteric tube is in place, the tip is out of the image but appears to be post-pyloric. The endotracheal tube has been removed.
